<section id="product-details" class="section-p1">
    <div class="container">
        <h4>Rubber Plant</h4>
        <img src="3_4017da1e-04de-4f56-998e-481dc4ad157b.webp" alt="Rubber Plant" class="product-img" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips:</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Light: Bright, indirect sunlight.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Water: Water when the top inch of soil is dry.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Temperature: Prefers temperatures between 60-75°F (15-24°C).</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Humidity: Enjoys high humidity but can adapt to average indoor humidity.</li>
            <li>Soil: Well-draining potting mix.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="container"> 
        <h4>Chinese Evergreen Crete</h4>
        <img src="Red-Chinese-Evergreen-4_c6832acb27c72430f782d679cd672ef1.webp" alt="Chinese Evergreen Crete" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">I'm a compact plant and a relatively slow grower but I could reach as high as 1m.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">I like medium to moderate light. If my leaves are dark, they can handle more light, if they're light, I'll only be able to tolerate medium light.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Keep my soil lightly moist constantly but be careful not to overwater me as my delicate roots are susceptible to rot.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Keep me away from draughts and in temperatures of between 18 and 24°C.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Please feed me diluted fertiliser once a month during the growing season.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <h4 style="color: #006400; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">Bromeliad</h4>
        <img src="bromeliad-indoors-950489120-fab1e3c5a0bd42d7a11e80720552acb2.webp" alt="Bromeliad" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">I'm a compact plant and a relatively slow grower but I could reach as high as 1m.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">I like medium to moderate light. If my leaves are dark, they can handle more light, if they're light, I'll only be able to tolerate medium light.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Keep my soil lightly moist constantly but be careful not to overwater me as my delicate roots are susceptible to rot.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Keep me away from draughts and in temperatures of between 18 and 24°C.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Please feed me diluted fertiliser once a month during the growing season.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

 <div class="container"> 
    <h4 style="color: #006400; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">Aloe Plants</h4>
    <img src="plants-that-dont-need-water-aloe-plant (1).webp" alt="Aloe Plants" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
    <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Light: Aloe plants need bright, indirect sunlight. They can tolerate some direct sunlight, especially in the morning, but too much direct sun can cause the leaves to turn brown.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Water: Water deeply but infrequently. Allow the top inch or two of soil to dry out completely between waterings. Overwatering can lead to root rot.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Temperature: Aloe plants prefer temperatures between 55-80°F (13-27°C). They can tolerate cooler temperatures but should be protected from frost.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Humidity: Aloe plants do well in low humidity. They are adapted to arid conditions and do not require additional humidity.</li>
        <li>Soil: Use a well-draining soil mix, such as a cactus or succulent mix. Adding perlite or sand to regular potting soil can improve drainage.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

    <div class="container"> 
        <h4 style="color: #006400; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">Orchids</h4>
        <img src="GettyImages-1368204335-_small.jpg" alt="Orchid" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Light: Bright, indirect sunlight.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Water: Once a week, allowing the potting medium to slightly dry out between waterings.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Temperature: 60-75°F (16-24°C) during the day, slightly cooler at night.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Humidity: High humidity levels, ideally between 50-70%.</li>
            <li>Soil: Well-draining mix with bark, perlite, and sphagnum moss.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="container"> 
        <h4 style="color: #006400; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">Rosemary (Salvia Rosmarinus)</h4> 
        <img src="Rosemary (Salvia Rosmarinus).png" alt="Rosemary (Salvia Rosmarinus)" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Light: Bright, indirect sunlight.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Water: Once a week, allowing the soil to slightly dry out between waterings.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Temperature: 60-75°F (16-24°C) during the day, slightly cooler at night.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Humidity: High humidity levels, ideally between 50-70%.</li>
            <li>Soil: Well-draining mix with bark, perlite, and sphagnum moss.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="container"> 
        <h4 style="color: #006400; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">Peace Lily</h4>
        <img src="Peace Lily.png" alt="Peace Lily" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style="color: #006400; margin-top: 20px;">Care Tips</h5>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Light: Bright sunlight.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Water: Once a week.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Temperature: 60-75°F (16-24°C).</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Humidity: 50-70%.</li>
            <li>Soil: Well-draining mix.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="container"> 
        <h4>Basil (Ocimum Basilicum)</h4>
        <img src="Basil (Ocimum Basilicum).png" alt="Basil (Ocimum Basilicum)" style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
        <h5 style=>Care Tips</h5>
        <ul>
            <li>Light: Thrives in bright sunlight, 6-8 hours daily.</li>
            <li>Water: Keep soil moist, not waterlogged.</li>
            <li>Temperature: Prefers 70-90°F (21-32°C).</li>
            <li>Humidity: Moderate humidity, mist occasionally.</li>
            <li>Soil: Well-draining soil mix.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>


